post_text: We are pleased to partner with the City of Pawucket to offer Blackstone Academy’s multipurpose room as an additional polling location for both the primary and general election on September 8th and November 3rd! This will help give Pawtucket neighbors safer options for voting this year. Also, Registrar Ken McGill is in great need of paid poll workers on those days! Call him at 728-0500 x283 and let him know you want to work that day! Finally, if you are not yet registered to vote, go here https://vote.sos.ri.gov/Home/RegistertoVote?ActiveFlag=1 to register online or get a paper ballot
shared_text:
VOTE.SOS.RI.GOV
Welcome to your Voter Information Center
text:
We are pleased to partner with the City of Pawucket to offer Blackstone Academy’s multipurpose room as an additional polling location for both the primary and general election on September 8th and November 3rd! This will help give Pawtucket neighbors safer options for voting this year. Also, Registrar Ken McGill is in great need of paid poll workers on those days! Call him at 728-0500 x283 and let him know you want to work that day! Finally, if you are not yet registered to vote, go here https://vote.sos.ri.gov/Home/RegistertoVote?ActiveFlag=1 to register online or get a paper ballot

post_text: BACS Families - we are submitting our first draft of our reopening plan to RIDE this afternoon. We will be sending info to all families within the next 1-2 weeks on the different reopening scenarios, once we get feedback from RIDE. We will be fully transparent with you and will incorporate your ideas and feedback. Thank you for your patience! It’s a big task! Student and staff safety is our #1 priority.

We will be sending info to all families within the next 1-2 weeks on the different reopening scenarios, once we get feedback from RIDE. We will be fully transparent with you and will incorporate your ideas and feedback. Thank you for your patience! It’s a big task! Student and staff safety is our #1 priority.

post_text:
We are working hard on our safe reopening plan for September and look forward to sharing it with families soon. In our proposed plan, students will be in the building 2-3 days per week and on distance learning 2-3 days per week. We will be scheduling optional Zoom calls for families to learn about the plan and give feedback. Stay tuned!
Estamos trabajando muy duro para desarrollar un plan seguro para abrir la escuela en septiembre. Anticipamos compartir este plan muy pronto con nuestras familias. En el plan, los estudiantes están en el edificio 2-3 días cada semana, y haciendo aprendizaje a distancia 2-3 días. Vamos a tener un Zoom opcional para familias para explicar el plan y escuchar sus opiniones. Estaremos en contacto!

post_text: The entire Blackstone Academy community stands for racial justice and fights for change that will dismantle systemic racism and create equal opportunities for people of color. In challenging times, BACS has always stayed strong and supported our community by being TOGETHER, by listening, by lifting up student voice, by educating, and by acting. It's harder now than ever not to be together. Care for yourselves, reach out if you need help, and know we are all together in our hearts. #blacklivesmatter

post_text: Please share these multilingual posters related to Covid-19 on your social media. Also, please share this phone number, particularly to anyone living in Central Falls and Pawtucket: (855)-843-7620. Residents can call this number and get questions answered in English, Spanish, Portuguese and Cape Verdean Creole. This phone number is safe for people to call and if you have a medical question, you only have to leave a phone number and someone will call you back. People can get access to testing in Pawtucket and Central Falls as well as rides to testing. This is particularly important for family members who do not have a primary care physician. Remember- all testing is free!

post_text:
Blackstone Academy Families,

Parents/Guardians should NOT be sending students to school if they are sick or have a fever. Students need to be fever-free (without meds) for 24 hours before coming to school. The RI Dept. of Health is asking families to communicate excused absences to schools, but a doctor's note is not required. Please call our main office with any questions, 401-726-1750.

Blackstone Academy Families,

Los padres / tutores NO deben enviar a los estudiantes a la escuela si están enfermos o tienen fiebre. Los estudiantes deben estar libres de fiebre (sin medicamentos) durante 24 horas antes de venir a la escuela. El Departamento de Salud de RI está pidiendo a las familias que comuniquen las ausencias justificadas a las escuelas, pero no se requiere una nota del médico. Por favor llame a nuestra oficina principal con cualquier pregunta, 401-726-1750.

post_text: Last week, 3 extraordinary Blackstone student artists were honored by the Natasha Love Foundation. Here they are with their families at the Carnival of Love Awards Dinner: Aaron Holloway: Visual Artist Award; Joshua Ortiz: Music Award; Quincy Smith: Visual Artist Award. Thanks to Gail Robinson for helping these students access this opportunity, including scholarship dollars ❤️🕺🥁👨‍🎨

post_text: We are thrilled to announce that Principal Kyleen Carpenter was one of 10% of applicants chosen to go with other school administrators to Finland for 10 days as part of the Fulbright Leaders Global Schools Program! Those of you who know her won’t be surprised that Kyleen is being recognized with this prestigious award. Blackstone Academy will also be represented as the leaders share their local school practices on an international level! https://www.irex.org/project/fulbright-leaders-global-schools-program

post_text:
Blackstone Academy wishes you a Happy New Year! In preparation for the final half of the school year, the Blackstone Academy Family Engagement Committee has prepared a quick survey to plan the rest of the 2019-2020 parent workshops. Your input would be very helpful as we move forward this year.

For English/Spanish, click on this link: https://forms.gle/ZJUchkj5WkXRHw739

For English/ Portugues, click on this link: https://forms.gle/PFxhf1fqRbKQdBbV6

If you have any questions, please contact Felicia Smith at fsmith@blackstoneacademy.org
Or Debbie Reyes at dreyes@blackstoneacademy.org.

We appreciate your time, thank you so much for completing the survey!
